        "description": {
            "value": "<p>You conjure a chilling mist that settles into the bones and makes it difficult to move. This has the effects of @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Mist], except that you can Sustain the spell once per round to move the fog up to 10 feet. A creature that starts its turn in the area takes 6d8 cold damage with a basic Fortitude save. A creature that fails its save is also @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Clumsy]{Clumsy 1} for 1 minute (@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Clumsy]{Clumsy 2} on a critical failure) and takes a –10-foot status penalty to Speeds for as long as it's clumsy.</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spell-effects.Item.Spell Effect: Frozen Fog]</p><hr /><p><strong>Heightened (+2)</strong> The damage increases by 3d8.</p>"
